args: Hey there, boss! Ready to make the most\noutta another glorious vacation day?
Heh. Someone woke up with a full head\nof steam. What do you have in mind?
Well, I figured I was gonna... Huh.
Hey, Cleo! Hang on a tick!\nWe was just tryin' to figure out—
Whoa, easy with the poker, lady!\nYou could gut a guy swingin' that\nthing around on a crowded beach!
Which is why you should never disturb\nsomeone while they are cooking.
Wait, yer cookin'? Here? Now?\nThis is a VACATION!
And do you wish to EAT on this vacation,\nor are you planning to subsist on sand?
Unfortunately, it seems I am the only one\nin this entire band who can prepare a\nsatisfying meal.
Yeah, I guess ya got a point there.\n...But, uh, maybe I can help?
Don't worry yourself about me, Ranzal.\nIn truth, I rather enjoy this sort of thing.
Now if you will excuse me,\nI have rice that needs steaming.
Cleo's been doing nothing but cooking\nfor everyone else since we got here.
Then I know what we're gonna do today!
So we can cook for Cleo?
Damn straight! We're ALL supposed to be\non vacation here, and she's earned herself\na good meal more'n just about anyone.
I love the idea—but if we're cooking\nfor Cleo, it all needs to be perfect.
And there ain't nothin' more perfect than\nGrillmaster Ranzal's Legendary BBQ!
You certainly don't lack for confidence.\nSo how can I help?
Well, since we're at the beach,\nwhat say ya do some fishin'?
I betcha we could catch all sorts of tasty\ntropical fish for our grill around here.
Oh wow, look how colorful this one is.\nI bet it tastes amazing!
Looks like ya hooked yerself a...
Ah, hellfire! Back off! Don't touch it!
'Cause it's more poisonous than a black\nwidow hitchin' a ride on a rattlesnake!
If ya even take a nibble or brush up\nagainst a fin, yer gonna be laid low\nfor a week and prayin' for death.
Which is what makes it so dangerous.\nTrust me—that fish ain't yer chum.
Still, don't feel bad—I know experienced\nanglers what made the same mistake.
I'm glad you were here to warn me.
Luckily I caught us a real tasty one\nwhile you were haulin' up that devil.
It looks... Hmm, what's the word...?\nDisgusting. Yeah, that's it.\nThat fish looks disgusting.
Bwaaa ha ha! Watch and learn, boss!\nThis fella's as tasty as he is ugly.
Here, lemme fry ya up a bite.
Oh my gosh. This is fantastic.
It's tender and almost sweet!\nHonestly, I sort of expected this\nto taste like the bottom of a shoe.
You certainly know a lot about fish.
Heh. S'pose I do, at that.
Anyway, that should be enough fish.\nLet's hunt down the next ingredient.
